        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">The Global production volume of pure hydrogen in 2020 is 71.3 Mt, about 72% are produced by steam methane refoming.
According to the HydrogenEurope (2022), about 90% of hydrogen are produced directly within the plant, it is assumed that only 10% reach the merchant market and are therefore compressed. This value was assumed to be representative for the Global geography

References:
IEA (2021): The Future of Hydrogen, available here: https://www.iea.org/reports/the-future-of-hydrogen.
U.S. Department of Energy (2020): Hydrogen strategy: Enabling low-carbon economy, available here: https://www.energy.gov/fecm/articles/hydrogen-strategy-enabling-low-carbon-economy.
Hydrogen Europe (2022): Clean hydrogen monitor 2022, available here: https://hydrogeneurope.eu/clean-hydrogen-monitor-2022/.</productionVolumeComment>
